<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FD5FE5B48A75106FE2BF83E" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FD5FE5B48A75106FABBF85A" blockId="411.[151,1437,1578,2035]" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD5FE5B48A75106FE0DF9B3" bold="true" box="[151,424,1578,1603]" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FD5FE5B4AB35106FD7BF9B2" box="[643,734,1578,1602]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" unit="mm" value="5.4">5.4 mm</quantity>
. Head brown, except mandible, clypeus, occiput and anterior region of face reddish; antenna black-brown, except segments 1–2 yellow-reddish; mesosoma and metasoma black, with reddish nuances on disc of pronotum; legs reddish, except coxae, clubs of femora and tibiae completely or partly brown. Antenna clavate. Head excavated, shiny, smooth, unsculptured; occipital carina absent. Palpal formula 6/3. Pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression, hairy, shiny, unsculptured. Scutum dull, sculptured by some longitudinal striae, laterally with two pointed apophyses. Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Metanotum transversely striate and hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, with deep median longitudinal furrow, with anterior surface unsculptured and posterior surface transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture distinct and complete. Protarsal segment 1 shorter than segment 4 (13:21). Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FD5FE5B4CEC5066FAFCF892" box="[1244,1369,1866,1890]" captionStart="PLATE 129" captionStartId="412.[151,233,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[251,1360,292,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-100@412.[151,1436,267,1919]" captionTargetPageId="412" captionText="PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Plate 129A</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and 11 peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FD5FE5B4BF65042FBE6F876" box="[966,1091,1902,1926]" captionStart="PLATE 129" captionStartId="412.[151,233,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[251,1360,292,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-100@412.[151,1436,267,1919]" captionTargetPageId="412" captionText="PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Plate 129A</figureCitation>
) with inner margin proximally not serrated, with two rows of about 40 lamellae; distal apex with at least 30 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FD5FE5B48F7509BFE2BF83E" blockId="411.[151,1437,1578,2035]" box="[199,398,1974,1999]" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD5FE5B48F7509BFEAEF83F" bold="true" box="[199,267,1975,1999]" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Male.</emphasis>
